- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on linear system identification, which is a topic within systems and control. 
- cs.ST (Statistics): The paper uses heavy-tailed probability density functions to model output measurement noise, which is a statistical approach. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a new maximum a posteriori (MAP) estimator and an iterative scheme based on the Expectation-Maximization (EM) method to solve the optimization problem, which are numerical methods. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a machine learning method for system identification, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence.
